news.title: Work on town planning scheme for Mann-Mhalunge to begin by year-end
news.para: The state government had recently approved the changes made in the town planning scheme as 29 plots had to be re-allocated as they were in the flood line area. Seventeen plots in Mann and twelve in Mhalunge were in the flood line area as per the earlier proposal which was objected to.

news.title: Indore: 50 objections received over proposal to increase collector's guideline
news.para: The district-level evaluation committee of Indore stamp and registrar department had on March 10 proposed a 10% rise in collector’s guideline of properties in 431 localities and 25% increase in 144 areas of Indore district.

news.title: Credai Aurangabad says e-charging norms will raise house prices
news.para: Credai said the installation of average quality e-charging station for an apartment of 10 flat could cost minimum Rs 30,000 to Rs 50,000.

news.title: Gurugram: Chintels Paradiso residents pool in money to file case in SC
news.para: Residents also alleged that members of the previous RWA nominated by the developer had been threatening to get the RWA’s bank account freezed to prevent them from filing the case against the developer.

news.title: Ghaziabad man promises possession of flats, dupes 51 of Rs 11 crore
news.para: According to deputy commissioner of police (EOW) MI Haider, the complainants alleged that directors of a firm named Manju J Homes Ltd had induced people to book flats in his proposed housing project, Red Apple Homez, in Ghaziabad.

news.title: Pune: EOW probes developer in Rs 200 crore cheating case
news.para: The Economic Offences Wing (EOW) has prima facie pegged the cheating amount at Rs200 crore. The cheating, according to the police, occurred between 1990 and February this year.

news.title: Survey illegal colonies & compile report, Haryana government tells town planners
news.para: Nearly 1,200 colonies, including 500 in Gurgaon and its surrounding areas such as Sohna, Farukhnagar, Pataudi and Bhondsi, have been registered on the portal to date.

news.title: UP-RERA microsite to hear out realtors on procedural delays
news.para: Just like it handles disputes between builders and buyers, Rera will also mediate with the authorities concerned when it gets complaints from developers on the microsite, officials said.

news.title: Income tax department seize unaccounted cash worth Rs 20 crore in Omaxe raids
news.para: Searches were believed to have been conducted at Omaxe’s offices in Noida, Gurugram, Indore, Chandigarh and other places. Sources said 38 other offices were still being searched on Tuesday evening.

news.title: Gurugram: STP seeks action against AIPL The Peaceful Homes' builder for layout changes
news.para: The developer also did not mention the objections raised by the residents in its undertaking to the department and got the changes approved in May last year.

news.title: Pune: Power supply to six government offices cut over dues, property registration hit
news.para: Deepak Patil, the manager of the government photo registry department, told TOI that total bill outstanding by all the six offices of the government photo registry department was Rs6.94 lakh.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP writes to IIT-Roorkee for structural audit of five projects
news.para: In the letter, senior town planner Sanjeev Mann requested SK Ghost, head of the civil engineering department at IIT-Roorkee, to constitute a team and conduct a structural audit of five societies — M3M Woodshire, Raheja Atharva and Vedaanta, Brisk Lumbini and Mahindra Aura — on an urgent basis.

news.title: Macrotech Developers repays offshore bonds worth $170 million
news.para: Real estate major Lodha Group, listed as Macrotech Developers, has redeemed offshore bonds of principal amount of $170 million or around Rs 1,300 crore. The company has repaid this debt nearly a year ahead of scheduled maturity of these bonds in March 2023.

news.title: Ramgarh locals demand amendment in building by-laws
news.para: On Monday, the building owners under the banner of Ramgarh Vikas Manch held a press conference where they said that they will soon announce the dates for the stir. “Builders and business community are living in fear due to CBR’s notice,” said a member.

news.title: So far, Rs 615 crore spent on Patna metro project: Bihar housing minister
news.para: Replying to a question of former Bihar deputy CM Sushil Kumar Modi in Rajya Sabha, the minister said the sanctioned cost of the project is Rs 13,365 crore, in which the central share is Rs 1,840 crore.
